claim.claim-text:
1. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor device, comprising the steps of:
forming a semiconductor layer on an insulating surface;
forming a gate insulating film on the semiconductor layer;
forming a first conductive film and a second conductive film on the gate insulating film;
etching the first conductive film and the second conductive film,
forming a first shape gate electrode composed of a first electrode and a second electrode on the semiconductor layer;
etching the first electrode and the second electrode, forming a second shape gate electrode composed of a third electrode and a fourth electrode;
adding an n-type impurity element to the semiconductor layer in a self aligning manner with the second shape gate electrode as a mask, forming an n-type impurity region containing a first concentration of the n-type impurity element;
forming a mask covering a portion of the semiconductor layer; and
forming on the semiconductor layer:
an n-type impurity region containing a second concentration of the n-type impurity element, adjacent to a channel forming region through the third electrode; an n-type impurity region containing a third concentration of the n-type impurity element, adjacent to the n-type impurity region containing the first concentration of the n-type impurity element; and
an n-type impurity region containing the third concentration of the n-type impurity element, adjacent to the n-type impurity region containing the second concentration of the n-type impurity element.

2. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor device, comprising the steps of:
forming a first semiconductor layer, a second semiconductor layer, a third semiconductor layer, and a fourth semiconductor layer on an insulating surface;
forming a gate insulating film on the first through the fourth semiconductor layers;
forming a first conductive film and a second conductive film on the gate insulating film;
etching the first conductive film and the second conductive film, forming a first shape gate electrode, composed of a first electrode and a second electrode, on the first through the fourth semiconductor layers;
etching the first electrode and the second electrode, forming a second shape gate electrode, composed of a, third electrode and a fourth electrode;
adding an n-type impurity element to the first through the fourth semiconductor layers in a self aligning manner, with the second shape gate electrode as a mask,
forming an n-type impurity region containing a first concentration of the n-type impurity element;
forming a first mask covering all of the second semiconductor layer and all of the fourth semiconductor layer, and forming a second mask covering a portion of the third semiconductor layer;
forming a second concentration impurity region through the third electrode with the fourth electrode on the first semiconductor layer as a mask, and an n-type impurity region containing a third concentration of the n-type impurity element, in the first semiconductor layer;
forming an n-type impurity region containing a second concentration of the n-type impurity element through the third electrode with the fourth electrode and the second mask as a mask, and an n-type impurity region containing the third concentration of the n-type impurity element, in the third semiconductor layer;
forming a third mask covering the first semiconductor layer and the third semiconductor layer; and
adding a p-type impurity element to the second semiconductor layer and to the fourth semiconductor layer, forming a p-type impurity region containing a first concentration of the p-type impurity element, and a p-type impurity region containing a second concentration of the p-type impurity element.

3. A method of manufacturing a semiconductor device comprising the steps of:
forming a first semiconductor layer, a second semiconductor layer, a third semiconductor layer, and a fourth semiconductor layer on an insulating surface;
forming a gate insulating film on the first through the fourth semiconductor layers;
forming a first conductive film and a second conductive film on the gate insulating film;
etching the first conductive film and the second conductive film, forming a first shape gate electrode, composed of a first electrode and a second electrode, on the first through the fourth semiconductor layers;
adding an n-type impurity element to the first through the fourth semiconductor layers with the first shape gate electrode as a mask, forming an n-type impurity region containing a first concentration of the n-type impurity element;
etching the first electrode and the second electrode, forming a second shape gate electrode, composed of a third electrode and a fourth electrode;
forming a first mask covering all of the second semiconductor layer and all of the fourth semiconductor layer, and forming a second mask covering a portion of the third semiconductor layer;
forming a second concentration impurity region through the third electrode with the fourth electrode on the first semiconductor layer as a mask, and forming an n-type impurity region containing a third concentration of the n-type impurity element, in the first semiconductor layer;
forming an n-type impurity region containing a second concentration of the n-type impurity element through the third electrode with the fourth electrode and the second mask as masks, and forming an n-type impurity region containing the third concentration of the n-type impurity element, in the third semiconductor layer;
forming a third mask covering the first semiconductor layer and the third semiconductor layer; and
adding a p-type impurity element to the second semiconductor layer and to the fourth semiconductor layer, forming a p-type impurity region containing a first concentration of the p-type impurity element, and a p-type impurity region containing a second concentration of the p-type impurity element.
